## Phase 3 — Theme Toggle Button (The Sexy Part ✨)

#### [MODIFY] [Sidebar.jsx](file:///home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend/src/components/Sidebar.jsx)

Add a smooth, animated toggle near the bottom of the sidebar, above the user card:

```jsx
import { useTheme } from './ThemeProvider.jsx';
import { Sun, Moon } from 'lucide-react';

// Inside the component:
const { theme, toggle } = useTheme();

// Add this JSX before the user card div:
<button
  onClick={toggle}
  className="w-full flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 rounded-lg
             text-white/60 hover:text-white hover:bg-white/5
             transition-all group"
  aria-label={`Switch to ${theme === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark'} mode`}
>
  <div className="relative w-[18px] h-[18px]">
    <Sun  size={18} className={`absolute inset-0 transition-all duration-300
          ${theme === 'light' ? 'opacity-100 rotate-0' : 'opacity-0 -rotate-90'}`} />
    <Moon size={18} className={`absolute inset-0 transition-all duration-300
          ${theme === 'dark'  ? 'opacity-100 rotate-0' : 'opacity-0 rotate-90'}`} />
  </div>
  <span className="text-sm font-medium">
    {theme === 'dark' ? 'Light Mode' : 'Dark Mode'}
  </span>
</button>
```

