## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
1. Run `npm run dev` from `/home/aarush_linux/projects/PBL/frontend`
2. Open the app in browser
3. Verify dark mode looks **identical** to current production
4. Click the theme toggle in the sidebar
5. Verify light mode renders correctly across all pages:
   - Overview / Executive Summary
   - Clauses list
   - Compare page
   - Reports page
   - Settings
   - Auth screens (login/register)
   - Chat popup
   - Loading overlay
   - Empty state
6. Toggle back to dark — verify nothing changed
7. Refresh the page — verify theme persists (localStorage)
8. Clear localStorage, set OS to light mode — verify auto-detection

### Visual Regression Spots to Watch
- Radar chart SVG grid lines visible in both modes
- Gauge arc backgrounds have good contrast in light mode  
- Glass card readability (text contrast ratios meet WCAG AA)
- Risk pills (`critical/moderate/low`) still pop on light backgrounds
- Auth overlay glow effect isn't too bright in light mode
- Scrollbar colors appropriate for light mode

